@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About Us";
}

<div class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
        <h1>About Sri Kaliyuga Ranganathar Temple</h1>
        <nav aria-label="breadcrumb">
            <ol class="breadcrumb">
                <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Index">Home</a></li>
                <li class="breadcrumb-item active">About Us</li>
            </ol>
        </nav>
    </div>
</div>

<section class="about-section py-5">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-6 mb-4">
                <img src="~/images/temple-facade.jpg.jpeg" alt="Temple Facade" class="img-fluid rounded temple-image">
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-6">
                <h2 class="section-title">Our History & Heritage</h2>
                <p class="lead">Sri Kaliyuga Ranganathar Temple stands as a beacon of spiritual devotion and cultural heritage, dedicated to Lord Ranganathar, the divine protector of devotees in Kaliyuga.</p>
                
                <p>Established with the divine vision of creating a sacred space for devotees to experience the grace of Lord Balaji, our temple has been serving the community for over two decades. The temple architecture reflects traditional South Indian temple design, incorporating sacred geometry and spiritual symbolism.</p>
                
                <p>Our temple follows the ancient Agama traditions and conducts daily rituals as prescribed in the sacred texts. The sanctum sanctorum houses a beautiful idol of Lord Venkateswara, crafted by skilled artisans following traditional methods.</p>
                
                <div class="temple-stats mt-4">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-6">
                            <div class="stat-item">
                                <h3 class="stat-number">25+</h3>
                                <p class="stat-label">Years of Service</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-6">
                            <div class="stat-item">
                                <h3 class="stat-number">50,000+</h3>
                                <p class="stat-label">Devotees Served</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="mission-section py-5 bg-light">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-4 mb-4">
                <div class="mission-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-eye mission-icon"></i>
                    <h4>Our Vision</h4>
                    <p>To be a spiritual sanctuary that nurtures devotion, promotes cultural values, and serves as a center for community welfare and spiritual growth.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4 mb-4">
                <div class="mission-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-bullseye mission-icon"></i>
                    <h4>Our Mission</h4>
                    <p>To provide a sacred space for worship, conduct traditional rituals, preserve cultural heritage, and serve devotees with dedication and devotion.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4 mb-4">
                <div class="mission-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-heart mission-icon"></i>
                    <h4>Our Values</h4>
                    <p>Devotion, Service, Tradition, Community, Spirituality, and Compassion guide all our activities and interactions with devotees.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="significance-section py-5">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-12">
                <h2 class="section-title text-center mb-5">Spiritual Significance</h2>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto">
                <div class="significance-content">
                    <h4>Lord Venkateswara - The Wish-Fulfilling Deity</h4>
                    <p>Lord Venkateswara, also known as Balaji, is revered as the preserver and protector of the universe. According to ancient scriptures, Lord Vishnu incarnated as Venkateswara to save humanity and grant the wishes of sincere devotees.</p>
                    
                    <h4>The Sacred Mantras</h4>
                    <p>The temple resonates with the chanting of sacred mantras including the Vishnu Sahasranamam, Venkatesa Suprabhatam, and various stotras that invoke divine blessings and spiritual purification.</p>
                    
                    <h4>Festivals and Celebrations</h4>
                    <p>Our temple celebrates all major Hindu festivals with special emphasis on Brahmotsavam, Vaikunta Ekadashi, and other Vishnu-related festivals, providing devotees with opportunities for spiritual elevation.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>